  "body": "#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: all\r\nOS & Version: all\r\nCommit hash : (if `develop`)\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nWhen calling a constant contract function from the go binder one should be able to set the sender address.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nWhen calling a constant contract function from the go binder a default sender address is used by geth, and address 0 is used by parity.\r\n\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\nMake a contract:\r\n\r\n```\r\ncontract TestPool{\r\n   function debug_me() constant returns(uint) {\r\n       return uint(msg.sender);\r\n   }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nCall \r\n```\r\n    sender, err := pool.Debug_me(nil)\r\n    if err != nil {\r\n        log.Fatalf(\"Failed to retrieve debug_me: %v\", err)\r\n    }\r\n    fmt.Println(\"sender:\", sender)\r\n```\r\n#### Backtrace\r\nIn parity\r\n````\r\n0\r\n````\r\nWith geth\r\n````\r\naccount[0]\r\n````\r\n",
